# Cognitive Agents in Malmo

This project is about setting up a robust connection between ACT-R and Malmo so that an ACT-R model in Lisp can received information from Minecraft and act on Minecraft environment.
* Malmo: An interface that allows interaction between Minecraft and Python, Lua, Java, etc. Installation instruction can be viewed in official project page
* ACT-R 7: A cognitive architecture based on a Unified Theory of Cognition by Alan Newell.

### Common Lisp dependencies
* JSON Network Interface: A module to communicate ACT-R with other languages through TCP.
* jsown
* bordeaux-threads
* usocket

### Python dependencies
* twisted
* PIL